$ Excel Object Model: Worksheet.filterMode

`ws.filterMode` evaluates to → development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes/boolean[`true`] if a → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Worksheet contains a filtered list whose criteria hide rows.

If the filter hides rows, they can be made visible again with `ws.→ Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Worksheet/showAllData[showAllData]`.

sa:
  The → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/AutoFilter[`autoFilter`] object.

  The StackOverflow question → https://stackoverflow.com/questions/39184392[Why does activesheet.filterMode return `false` when sheet has filter?]
